    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 272.2 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>When Double Care is Needed</strong>&mdash;Children who have lost the one in whose breasts maternal love has flowed have met with a loss that can never be supplied. But when one ventures to stand in the place of mother to the little stricken flock, a double care and burden rests upon her to be even more loving if possible, more forbearing of censure and threatening than their own mother could have been, and in this way supply the loss which the little flock have sustained.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"2T 58.2\" data-link=\"120.242\">Ibid., 2:58</span>.</span></a></sup>",
